events.name: GDG Cloud Louisville Kick-off
events.description:
Join us for the GDG Cloud Louisville Kick-off event.
We will provide light refreshments and snacks. This is the first GDG Cloud Louisville meetup so we'll do brief introductions, gather input from the commmunity on what they value from the group to shape future meetings, and then dig into a technical topic of interest.
events.how_to_find_us: Main St entrance is next to the PNC building parking garage (just east of Starbucks).

events.name: Developing serverless style in GCP
events.description: We'll provide light snacks and soft drinks. Also, feel free to bring your laptop if you want to follow along and build your own serverless functions.
events.how_to_find_us: Main St entrance is next to the PNC building parking garage (just east of Starbucks).

events.name: 2019 GDG Cloud Louisville Kick-off
events.description:
Kick-off the the new year at GDG Cloud Louisville.
We're looking for guest speakers and topics, so please message me if you're interested in leading a session.
events.how_to_find_us: Main St entrance is next to the PNC building parking garage (just east of Starbucks).

events.name: GDG Cloud Louisville - Using AI services in GCP
events.description:
This month, we have a special guest speaker from Google. Virginia will present an overview and demonstrate how to use a few of the AI services in GCP. Please join us.
Also, I know several attendees have reported that GPS does not direct to the proper location based on address so please note the updated directions.
events.how_to_find_us: Start at the intersection of 4th/Main St (south side), head west on Main St. On your left will be Humana Digital Experience center. Door is at the end of the glass just before the entrance into PNC garage. If you get to Starbucks, too far.

events.name: GDG Cloud Louisville - Developing the Google Assistant
events.description:
This month, Aakash S. will present an overview and demonstrate how to develop interactions for the Google Assistant. Please join us.
